description: Two men have been arrested on suspicion of murder after a woman in her 50s was found dead.
title: Murder arrests after woman found dead
title_page: Southport: Murder arrests after woman found dead in property - BBC News
maintext:
Two men have been arrested on suspicion of murder after a woman was found dead.
Police officers were called to a home in Meols Cop Road in Southport at about 18:00 GMT on Wednesday after the ambulance service reported a woman, in her 50s, had been found.
Merseyside Police said it was currently treating her death as "unexplained" but "inquiries are ongoing to establish the full circumstances".
A 48-year-old man from Kirkdale and a 60-year-old man from Ainsdale were arrested but have since been released on bail.
